name: H.Res.753 [117th]
text: - Expressing support for the designation of October 28 as "Oxi Day" to commemorate the anniversary of Greek Prime Minister Ioannis Metaxas' answer of "Oxi!" or "No!" to surrender to the Axis forces, inflicting a fatal wound that helped save democracy for the world.

name: H.Res.757 [117th]
text: - Expressing the sense of the House of Representatives that Congress should enact the Voters with Disabilities Bill of Rights to establish that voters with disabilities have equal access to the ballot as nondisabled persons.

name: H.Res.756 [117th]
text: - Supporting the designation of October 27, 2021, as "National Civics Day".
